second meeting of the Constitutional R are rm Committee,
Thomas presented a draft of
his new constitution.
At the same meeting, the committee also considered a bill
presented to it earlier by Neil
kitchen.
kitchen's bill would have created the position of Ombudsman in the Student Guvem—
ment.
An Ombudsman is a people’s
projector in Scandinavian na.
tions who scrutinize: complaints
by individuals who think they
have been changed by the
bureaucracy. Two student got.
elements, N.Y.U. and the u.
of Colorado, and several states
in the Union have proposed
Ombudsman or Public projectors.
Both kitchen’s bill and Thos
mas’s draft were accepted by
the constitutional committee and
drawn up into one constitution.
