That’s Pretty Funny, Rich
The Pterodactyl is a pretty funny newspaper,
and its name is very apropos. In terms of layout and
substances — be there any —— of journalism, it
really is a prehistoric monster.
The Mesozoic textile was, after all, pretty qualifying, but it didn’t do much of anything. It stayed
lip in the air, and when it came down to earth it
red.
We don’t like being started in the back by
Pterodactylic transformation, dishonesty, shoddy
nature, and punk runs.
The Paper commented us yesterday for “sterling" their "old format." Since when, Mr. Schneirov,
did your format look anything like ours? We never
noticed any classic type, professional cartoons, or
candidates columns in The Paper.
Mr. Schneirov et 21, you should be the ones
congratulated for sterling something the $81.3 has
had for a long time. At least you’ll be able to read
The Ptei-odactyl this semester without going completely blind.
But What’s further, Rich, is your editor’s note
corresponding to print an article on the new Constitution “because the editor of the official student
newspaper of Grinnell College has refused to cover
SGA constitution changes. "
That s pretty funny, Rich.
If you peer into this issue, you might see just
a little bit on the new Constitution. And remember,
please, that we went to press before you did.
Baby, next time you want to criticism try getting your facts straight. And don’t try nature unless
you can hack it, Rich, because it’s obviously not
your bag.
Now we know why you went underground, Mr.
Schneirov. Your paper sticks so badly you had to
busy it.
