CRAWFORD ON THE PROBLEM
By ZELTE CRAWFORD
(Sociology)
Recent developments between
the Grinnell Community and the
Grinnell metro have brought
to the surface on issue that has
existed for some time, That
issue is the apparent tension
that has been building up be.
green the two sections for number of years,
Most people on Gﬂuncle’s campus will probably agree that
something should be done to
change this situation, Presently, however, the disagreement
 
 
ZELTE CRAWFORD
tests on the subject of what
change should be initiated, and
who Should indicate it,
Some circles propose that the
metro work more or less inde«
perfectly in searching for the
