now/WM 2‘
Although I maintain several major reservations
against the proposed constitution changes adopted
by the Senate, 1 do not necessarily urge defeat of
the proposal through student body ieierendum.
Student government at Grinnell friendly needs
a more liable operating mechanism, and the interesting oi the Senate with legislative authority is
consistent with the idea of distribution govexm
mental power among the Senate and the joint
boardsi With son elections rapidly approaching, a
new method of election hall officers in conjunction
with residence hall innovations is an immediate ne«
density.
I believe an additional positive factor in the proposed revision is the establishment of the office of
student coordinator a position investigated by the
ever-expanding administrative functions at the SGA
and by the lack of communication between various
faculty and student government committees and the
student body itself,
Putting aside for a moment these practical considerations, there are several facets of the proposed
revision which need careful scrutinyi creating the
ten senators tit-large will mean that thirty—one flu<
sent ofﬁyes, or nearly every inﬂcentral campus pas
action, will be elected by the student body as a
Whole.
Personal acquaintance and an intimate knowledge of views could easily lease to be determining
factors in all individual's election. An essential criterion for election In the Senate could become,
Literature, merely the maintenance of a campus
“name” for himself.
I must also question the ability of these ten enlarge senators to effectively ascertain campus opinion on major issues. Although certain more or less
artificial means for entertaining this opinion have
been provided, i.e. required attendance by senators
at all house meetings, I feel that hall representation is interested better suited for the effective represeiltatlon oi student viewpoints.
I repeat that the advantages and improvements
suggested by this proposed revision are indeed nu—
versus, certainly more numerous and wellrfounded
than the practical considerations mentioned abovei
A5 Student interest,
Contact. and involvement are
essential components of an effective student government organization, each student must decide
whether this new Senate and the office at student
coordinator can best promote these components.
 
