By J. VON ERIESEN RAZ
The chess master combines a unique set of parents, personality
trails, and abstract abilities, which he sessions into a highly differentiated system of thinking and playing methods.
initially, he is dealing in a subject matter composed of score
magic spatial (two- dimensional) possibilities for movement.
To the chess board he brings two facilities which are relatively
discrimination: a high non-verbal intelligence and a powerful
memory capacity. The high universal intelligence is furthermore
manchester in two forms: a spatial memory and a construction
spatial imagination. The distinction made here is that the complex
abstract images with which the player works can hardly be considered either textile or visual. By anatomy, the chess master is to
visual images as the speed reader is to programming each word.
The powerful memory capacity can probably be better understood when it is seen that it enables the master to learn program<
simply by experience, to refine his operating rules constantly by
means of the mental operations of instruction and rehabilitation
It a high rate.
The above congratulations are commonly understood by those
who have had relatively little or no experience with the game.
There is, however, another facility processed by the chess master
which is often overlooked and warranty our attention.
The pendant oi generating hypothesis is testing them. For ex.
apple, over the board the choice of a good move tests largely on
forestry possibilties for action and on the evaluation of forestry
results. The thought process is essentially an empirical investigation — there is no a priori or detective way to establish with her<
twenty how much can be obtained or how much can be proved (at
this point the problem of chess is strikingly different from that of a
mathematics problem). It is an investigation which terminates in a
decision necessarily based upon incomplete evidence, and necessarily directed towards quantities results.
 
